		<!--
                            <p>The story of Face Off begins in 2002. Two company actors at a small regional theatre in Port Jefferson, NY, created a short-form improvisational comedy show in the theater's unused second stage called "Friday Night Face Off". Little did they know that ten years later 'FNFO' would become the longest running, weekly improv show in Long Island history. In July of 2009, Eric and Jay formed Face Off Unlimited, LLC (a limited liability company). Jay was named Artistic Director and Eric CFO, and shortly thereafter they brought on the services of experienced improviser and former "FNFO" Creative Director Joe Teixeira as Director of Operations. Since then, the Face Off Universe has grown to include the following productions:</p>
                  -->

<!-- BATSU SHOW START -->
                  <div id="post-1" class="blog-post">
							  <div class="title">
								<h2><a href="./article.html">Face Off Unlimited Presents BATSU!</a></h2>
								</div>
								<a class="post-image" href="batsu.html">
									<img height="200" width="200" alt="Thumb1" src="./images/shows_batsu.png" />
								</a>
								<div class="post-detail">
								  <div class="post-info">
										<ul>
											<li class="date">Mondays and Thursdays at 8 PM</li>
											
											<li class="tags"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=Je+Bon+Noodle+House&hl=it&hq=Je+Bon+Noodle+House&radius=15000&t=h&z=17&iwloc=A" title="Je'Bon Noodle House" target="_blank">Je'Bon Noodle House</a></li>
										</ul>
								  </div>
									<p class="excerpt">
								  In Japan, batsu means "punishment" and the batsu-game is a form of comedy competition where the losers are forced to endure hilarious and outrageous penalties. Face Off Unlimited has blended this wildly popular piece of Japanese culture with their own hysterical style of improv comedy to create BATSU!
<br/><br/>
BATSU! takes place in a cool underground lounge theatre in NYC's "Little Tokyo.‚Äù  A full menu/bar is available and audience members enjoy sushi, noodles, and sake, while the bravest may even sign up for a chance to participate in the show to win free beer and prizes! Visit <a href="http://www.jebonusa.com" target="_blank">jebonusa.com</a> to view menu. 
									<div style="width:500px ; float:left"> <a href="batsu.html"><img src="images/more_button.png" width="89" height="33" alt="Read More" /></a></div>												
                        </div>
								</div>
<!-- BATSU SHOW END -->

<!-- IN THE ROOM SHOW START -->
                                <div id="post-2" class="blog-post">
								<div class="title">
									<h2><a href="http://intheroomwithus.com/" target="_blank">In The Room (with Joe Jay Eric and Lyle)</a></h2>
									
								</div>
								<a href="http://www.intheroomwithus.com/" target="_blank" class="post-image">
									<img height="200" width="200" alt="Thumb1" src="images/shows_intheroom2.png" />
								</a>
							  <div class="post-detail">
								  <div class="post-info">
										<ul>
											<li class="date">Every Saturday and Sunday</li>
											<li class="tags"><a href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/in-room-joe-jay-eric-lyle/id540297549" title="iTunes" target="_blank">iTunes</a></li>
										</ul>
								</div>
									<p class="excerpt">Join Face Off's Joe Tex, Jay Painter, and Eric Robinson as they discuss their opinions and observations of the world around them with radio personality and comedy writer Lyle Pinder. In the Room features original comedy content and often times features special guests stopping by to hang with the guys. 
<br/><br/>
Recent Roommates include: Jim Rash (Community), Joel Murray (Monsters University/God Bless America), Dan Bakkedahl (Legit/Veep), Josh Gad (1600 Penn, Book of Mormon, Jobs), Samm Levine (Do No Harm, Freaks & Geeks), Tyler Posey (Teen Wolf, Taco Shop),  Who will be in the ROOM next? Tune in every Saturday and Sunday to find out! 
<br/><br/>
Stream right from our website, or subscribe & download on iTunes & Stitcher.   Rate and subscribe the podcast rocketing up the iTunes "What's Hot" charts!
									
